status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment: I think the rootcause is non-determinism of hash() in Python. We may want to consider this test as inherently flaky and a retry decorator akin to https://github.com/apache/beam/blob/2f9d7112bc03b94c419eb48805972f7792d57b7d/sdks/python/apache_beam/runners/worker/statesampler_test.py#L41. Alternatively, tests should supply a deterministic hash function to ApproximateUniqueTest.

test_approximate_unique_global_by_sample_size is also flaky:
